# Session [13] – Network+

## Main Topics
- IP Header chist?  
- Field haye mohem dar IP Header  
- Tarze kar IP Header dar packet forwarding  

## Flashback – IP Header Basics
- IP Header = section az packet ke **information baraye routing va delivery** ra dare  
- Har IP packet dar layer 3 (Network Layer) header dare  

## Explanation

### Mohem-tarin Field ha
- **Version** = IPv4 ya IPv6  
- **Header Length (IHL)** = size header (chand 32-bit words)  
- **Total Length** = size kol packet (header + data)  
- **Source IP** = IP device ferestande  
- **Destination IP** = IP device giriye  
- **TTL (Time To Live)** = chand hop packet mitavanad beravad  
- **Protocol** = TCP/UDP/ICMP etc.  
- **Checksum** = baraye error detection  

### Tarze Kar
- Routers va devices header ro mikhonand ta packet ro be destination dorost ersal konand  
- TTL baraye prevent looping dar network  
- Checksum baraye ensure kardan ke header kharab nashode  

### Moghayese IPv4 va IPv6
| Field | IPv4 | IPv6 |
|-------|------|------|
| Version | 4 | 6 |
| Header Length | 20–60 bytes | Fixed 40 bytes |
| TTL | TTL | Hop Limit |
| Checksum | Yes | No |
| Source/Destination | 32-bit | 128-bit |

